  "prompt": "What is the difference between straight leg jeans and tapered leg jeans?",
  "response": "The main differences between straight leg and tapered leg jeans are:\n\nStraight Leg Jeans:\n- Cut is consistent from the knee to the ankle\n- Maintains same width from hip to hem\n- Provides a more relaxed, classic fit\n- Looks more traditional and squared off\n\nTapered Leg Jeans:\n- Gradually narrows from the knee to the ankle\n- Becomes slimmer toward the bottom of the leg\n- Fits closer to the leg's natural shape\n- Creates a more modern, streamlined appearance\n- Often looks more fitted and contemporary\n\nThe choice depends on personal style, body type, and preference for how the jeans look and feel.",
